dymm.doc.inspirations.vanilla.tweaks.flo:
Comparators can react to the contents of the flower pot. The possible values are:
- 0: empty;
- 1: mushroom;
-4: fern;
- 7: flower;
- 10: dead bush;
- 12: sapling;
- 15: cactus.

dymm.doc.quark.vanilla.experimental.coll:
When a Piston extends or retracts, blocks around it react like Slime Blocks (according to configuration settings).

The available behaviors are:
-above;
-below;
-above_below;
-above_edge;
-below_edge;
-above_below_edge;
-directional;
-sides;
-horizontals;
-verticals.

dymm.doc.quarkoddities.mod.oddities.item:
Transports items from one point to another, according to a set of rules:
- If an item can go down, it will always go down;
- At an intersection, an item will go forward if possible, otherwise either left or right randomly;
- An item will never go up unless that's the only possibility;
- Items can reach full inventories, in which case they'll turn around;
- At the end of a pipe, if such a pipe is not connected to anything, the item will pop out.

Pipes can also be disabled with redstone: a disabled pipe will not count when calculating the path.

Pipes can also be moved by Pistons are retain the items inside when this is done.

Too many items inside a pipe will cause it to break.
